description: Number of d dividing n such that d>=3 and 1<=n/d<=d-2.
links: Nathaniel Johnston, Table of n, a(n) for n = 1..10000
maple: with(numtheory): for n from 1 to 200 do it := divisors(n): count := 0: for i from 1 to nops(it) do if it[i]>=3 and 1<=n/it[i] and n/it[i]<=(it[i]-2) then count := count+1 fi :od: printf(`%d,`,count) od:
author: _Naohiro Nomoto_
extensions: More terms from _James A. Sellers_, Jun 20 2000
